@NODE Briefly "Briefly"

                @{b}Briefly@{ub}


    This is a collection of Anims and Buttons for ReqAttack in the style of your favourite
icon collection, plus a few other bits I thought might be useful. 

    (Brief enough?)


    < @{"  Front Page    " LINK Main}
    > @{"  Introduction  " LINK Introduction}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

                @{b}Introduction to Fuzzy GlowAttack@{ub}


    If you don't like reading long intoductions try this one @{"  Not so detailed Intro  " LINK ShortIntro}

    Well firsty I want to thank you for looking at this pack as it's my first attempt at
supplying the Amiga community with any form of software at all.

    Anybody remember a program called 'Arq'? Great wasn't it. Well, after that got a bit
long in the tooth another program with the same idea came along called 'MRQ'. This looked
nicer but kept on crashing, on my system at least so, personally, I just left that one.

    Enter ReqAttack.... Now that's more like it.

    This, as you may have gathered by the REALLY brief @{"  Brief  " LINK Briefly} page (Yes twice), this
is a collection of Buttons and Anims for ReqAttack v1.80+. You will need v1.80+ due to the
"Child" feature (It'll make sense if you use it).

    Over the months I have gathered up tons (In bytes) of Glow icons and many other forms
of Glow type images and a months ago decided, since I hadn't seen any "Glows" for ReqAttack,
to get a set of Anims on the go.

    Not long after I decided to do this a set of "MI" Anims arrived on the AmiNet. I was
expecting a nice looking package that would do the trick nicely but to my surprise it wasn't
as adventurous as I first presumed it would -or could- have been. There were only a few small
Anims that couldn't possibly cover the many requesters that are thrown our way in every day
(And not so everyay) use so off I went on my little er.... crusade.

    So, what do they look like you ask? Well have a little look in here @{"  Example  " LINK "GlowAttackExtras/Example/MAIN"}

    Now you might be thinking, "Oh, he's just got a load of Glow icons and converted them
into RAAnims (ReqAttack Anims for those that don't know). Well to start with I did. But
then things started to get a bit out of hand. Instead of simply having a 2 frame anim which
consisted of "No glow, Glow, No Glow, Glow...etc..." I changed them to all no Glow.... Then
PART of the image to Glow again (The bit that seemed important to the Anim/Requester), these
looked nice, so I kept them.


    Enjoy.


    < @{"  Front Page    " LINK Main}
    > @{"  Requirements  " LINK Requirements}
@ENDNODE

