@NODE Requirements "GlowAttack Requirements"

                @{b}GlowAttack Requirements@{ub}


    @{b}The absolute must have list@{ub}

    - An Amiga with the appropriate specification to run...

    - ReqAttack v1.80+ (http://uk.aminet.net/pub/aminet/util/misc/ReqAttack.lha)

    - The GlowAttack pack, without it you won't be able to use it ;o)


    @{b}The (Believe it or not) optional list@{ub}

    - ReqAttackPrefs v1.80+ to use/edit/configure the prefs file

    - RAAnimbrush.datatype and RABrush.datatype to view the images without using ReqAttack

    - Directory Opus 5.5+ to use the file type (http://www.gpsoft.com.au)

    - 'r' in your path to use the file type (http://uk.aminet.net/pub/aminet/util/cli/r.lha)
    

    < @{"  Front Page  " LINK Main}
    > @{"  Contents    " LINK Contents}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Contents "Contents"

                @{b}Contents of the GlowAttack package@{ub}


    - Those 2 frame RAAnims again, no borders this time. Some system and some programs.

    - Big and small button images (More variety to come)

    - A prefs file for you to load into RAPrefsMUI so you can use the above immediatley

    - A DOpus file types (Same as the ones in ReqAttack but with RMB options)

    - This Guide and a @{"  ReadMe  " LINK "ReadMe.txt/MAIN"}

    - An @{"  Example  " LINK "GlowAttackExtras/Example/MAIN"} picture

    - Some little scripts all to do with the instalation page


    < @{"  Front Page   " LINK Main}
    > @{"  Instalation  " LINK Instalation}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Instalation "Instalation"

                @{b}Installing the GlowAttack package@{ub}


    Boy did this bit just get simple for you lot!! (With a little help from JayC)

    First I'd suggest deleting the old package as I have changed the directory structure a
little bit and if you don't you'll have some files just sitting there getting bored.


    @{b}The following buttons on this page copy and delete files if, like me, you'd prefer
to do it manually don't click.@{ub}

    * If a "ReqAttack.prefs_backup" file exists I will copy it into the ReqAttack directory,
      just in case you still haven't made up your mind about the package *

    - Clicking here bring will up a requester, locate your ReqAttack path and I'll delete the
      old files for you @{"  Remove Old  " LINK ConfirmRemove}

    - Clicking here will throw another requester up, locate your ReqAttack path and all will
      be copied within a few clicks of... Lets just say a hard drive clicking @{"  Install  " SYSTEM "Execute GlowAttackExtras/Install"}


    Now close this guide and load the one you have just copied into "ReqAttack" and head onto
the "usage" page. (Really, it makes a difference).


    < @{"  Front Page  " LINK Main}
    > @{"  Usage       " LINK Usage}
@ENDNODE

@NODE ConfirmRemove "Are you sure ? ? ? ? ? ?"

                @{b}Think about it!!@{ub}


    Clicking THIS button will delete (not move/copy) all the files and directories:

    <ReqAttack path>/GlowAttack/#?
                    /GlowAttackExtras/#?    * See note below
                    /GlowAttack.guide
                    /GlowAttack.txt
                    /DirList.txt

    If you have placed any of your OWN files in these directories they will be deleted

    * If your "ReqAttack.prefs_backup" file exists I will copy it into the ReqAttack
      directory, just in case you still haven't made up your mind about the package

    You can view the script if you really want to @{"  Yes please  " LINK "GlowAttackExtras/RemoveOld/MAIN"}


    Are you sure you want to remove the old package ? ? ? @{"  I AIN'T SCARED  " SYSTEM "Execute GlowAttackExtras/RemoveOld"}

    You can do this manually if you want to know exactly what's going on.


    < @{"  Instalation  " LINK Instalation}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "How to use the package"

                @{b}How to use the GlowAttack anims@{ub}


    Now you've followed the instalation procedure and loaded this guide from the "ReqAttack"
directory (You have done that haven't you?) you can use the images.


    @{b}The following buttons on this page copy the files into the right place so you can use
them if, like me, you'd prefer to do it manually don't click.@{ub}


    - If you want 2 Frame anims click @{"  Here  " SYSTEM "Execute GlowAttackExtras/Use2Frame"} (You should use this first)

    - If you want Medium anims click  @{"  Here  " SYSTEM "Execute GlowAttackExtras/UseMedium"} (Not too many yet)

    - If you want Large anims click   @{"  Here  " SYSTEM "Execute GlowAttackExtras/UseLarge"} (Still only 1)


    - Now decide if you want @{"  Big  " SYSTEM "Copy GlowAttack/Buttons_Big/#? Buttons"} or @{"  Small  " SYSTEM "Copy GlowAttack/Buttons_Small/#? Buttons"} button images (Big buttons are shown in
      the @{"  Example  " LINK "GlowAttackExtras/Example/MAIN"}

    @{b}If you want to configure Reqttack yourself you can skip the next part@{ub}


    - You can now backup YOUR prefs file just in case you don't like mine by clicking @{"  Here  " SYSTEM "Copy ENVARC:ReqAttack.prefs GlowAttackExtras/ReqAttack.prefs_backup"}
        (Your prefs will be copied to the "GlowAttackExtras" directory)

    - Now copy my prefs to @{"  ENVARC:  " SYSTEM "Copy GlowAttackExtras/ReqAttack.prefs ENVARC:"} and if you don't want to have to reboot @{"  ENV:  " SYSTEM "Copy GlowAttackExtras/ReqAttack.prefs ENV:"}
    * You might still have to reboot if you have caches turned on in ReqAttack *


    > @{"  Some Extra Bits  " LINK Extras}

    < @{"  Front Page       " LINK Main}
    > @{"  Changes          " LINK Changes}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Extras "Some Extra Bits"

                @{b}Those extras I mentioned@{ub}


    Here's a couple of other things for you too.


    - If you want to use my DOpus file type click @{"  Here  " SYSTEM "Copy GlowAttackExtras/Picture_ReqAttackImage DOpus5:Filetypes"}
        (It's has a different filename so if you don't want it you can simply delete it)

    - @{"  Create  " SYSTEM "List GlowAttack/ ALL FILES NODATES >DirList.txt"} a list of the FuzzyGlowAnims you have (Handy to keep track of updates... I think)

    - @{"  View    " LINK "DirList.txt/MAIN"} the list of FuzzyGlowAnims in your collection


    @{b}De-instalation@{ub}


    - You don't like my prefs eh? If you want your previously backup one click @{"  Here  " SYSTEM "Copy GlowAttackExtras/ReqAttack.prefs_backup ENVARC:ReqAttack.prefs"}

    - Delete the "Picture_ReqAttackImage" file type from your DOpus5:Filetypes directory
        (If you've used it)

    - Delete all the GlowAttack files and directories from youor ReqAttack directory


    ^ @{" Usage      " LINK Usage}

    < @{" Front Page " LINK Main}
    > @{" Changes    " LINK Changes}
@ENDNODE

@NODE DeInstalation "Are you dumping me?"

                @{b}Had enough of Fuzzy GlowAttack?@{ub}


    This is where you can remove GlowAttack because it's crap. ;o)


    You can view the script if you really want to @{"  Yes please  " LINK "GlowAttackExtras/RemoveOld/MAIN"}


    So..... Remove GlowAttack??? @{"  I don't want to but the voices are telling me to  " SYSTEM "Execute GlowAttackExtras/Remove"}

        If you have clicked the above button to remove GlowAttack there will still be the
    "ReadMe.txt" and GlowAttack.guide files to delete, you'll have to do this manually.


    < @{"  Usage  " LINK Usage}
@ENDNODE

